title: The Dark Knight Rises - Main Themes (Piano Cover)
description:
00:00 On Thin Ice / 02:35 Gotham's Reckoning / 04:20 The Fire Rises / 04:45 Mind If I Cut In? / 05:48 Imagine The Fire / 06:50 The Shadows Betray You / 08:25 Why Do We Fall? / 09:35 Rise
Hello, I'm a huge fan of The Dark Knight Trilogy. I love the movies, the story, the actors, the themes and especially the music. Although I've listen to all three soundtracks maybe 500 times each, I think I prefer the third. I'm not sure why, but maybe I hear a maturity in it. After all, it had been almost 10 years since Zimmer was into this world, and in my opinion it shows. We can hear the growth of Bruce Wayne and his struggles so well in this score.

I'm a big fan of the complet score. It is basically the entirety of the music produced for the film and if you haven't heard these pieces it's really worth it. I suggest Bar Shootout, Batman Chased, A Dark Knight Suite, Cat Suite and Moody Bruce Transfiguration Suite part 1&2...just to name a few. But honestly if you love this music you'll love the entire score.

I not 100% happy with my performance, but I think I got the energy in it.

Thanks a lot for watching.
I'm just doing this for fun, by ear, so no sheets sorry.
Hope you like it!
